main event: A bright white light was observed circling the moon in Seattle, Washington on August 13, 1965.
interesting points: The object was initially mistaken for a planet before being identified as a U.F.O.,The sighting lasted for approximately 15 minutes,The sky conditions were described as clear,The observer noted that the object appeared as a solid, bright white light,The sighting was classified as inconclusive by Project Blue Book.
witness description: the object was initially thought to be a planet and was described as solid and white
